      • addProvider

        public <TProvider extends Provider> BootstrapScope addProvider​(java.lang.Class<TProvider> providerClass,
                                                               java.util.function.Function<Scope,​TProvider> supplier)
        Description copied from interface: BootstrapScope
        Registers a new provider implementation for the given class with the given provider.

        Existing providers matching the provider class type will be overwritten, but only if the class is an exact match.

        Use the BootstrapScope.addSingletonProvider(Class, Provider) method to register singleton providers or handle the lifetime of your provider with the calls to the provided supplier. 

        
 add(Scheduler.class, (scope) -> new BukkitScheduler(scope));
 // this will not overwrite the provider and both will be retrieved depending on the parameter of the get call
 add(BukkitScheduler.class, (scope) -> new BukkitScheduler(scope));
        Specified by:
        addProvider in interface BootstrapScope
        Type Parameters:
        TProvider - the type of the provider
        Parameters:
        providerClass - the class of the provider
        supplier - the supplier that creates the provider
        Returns:
        this bootstrap scope

      • addSingletonProvider

        public <TProvider extends Provider> BootstrapScope addSingletonProvider​(java.lang.Class<TProvider> providerClass,
                                                                        TProvider provider)
        Description copied from interface: BootstrapScope
        Registers a new singleton provider for the given class.

        Existing providers matching the provider class type will be overwritten, but only if the class is an exact match.

        Use the BootstrapScope.addProvider(Class, Function) method to register providers with different lifetimes. 

        
 Scheduler scheduler = new BukkitScheduler();
 add(Scheduler.class, scheduler);
 // this will not overwrite the provider and both will be retrieved depending on the parameter of the get call
 add(BukkitScheduler.class, scheduler);
        Specified by:
        addSingletonProvider in interface BootstrapScope
        Type Parameters:
        TProvider - the type of the provider
        Parameters:
        providerClass - the class of the provider
        provider - the provider instance that should be registered
        Returns:
        this bootstrap scope

      • load

        public ArtContext load​(java.lang.String key,
                       java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> list)
                throws ParseException
        Description copied from interface: Scope
        Loads the given string list and tries to parse each line into a valid art object.

        Uses the provided storage key to store the data of the context and reference it in future uses. Make sure to pass in the same storage key for all loads that need to persist data across sessions.

        Use the resulting ArtContext to ArtContext.execute(Object...), ArtContext.test(Object) or listen ArtContext.onTrigger(Class, TriggerListener).

        Specified by:
        load in interface Scope
        Parameters:
        key - the unique storage key for this provided input
        list - the list of valid art that is parsed into an art context
        Returns:
        the parsed art context
        Throws:
        ParseException - if the parse operation of the input fails
        See Also:
        Scope.load(String, Collection)

      • configuration

        public Configuration configuration()
        Description copied from interface: Scope
        The current configuration of this scope.

        The configuration is never null but may change during the lifetime of the scope. Directly access the configuration from the scope when you need it and do not cache it in a variable.

        The configuration may change when the scope is being bootstrapped, but should stay the same after bootstrapping has finished.

        Specified by:
        configuration in interface Scope
        Returns:
        the current configuration of this scope
